<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-3474] StackOverflowError with mixins and closures</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3474</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The following code throws StackOverflowError. Changing visibility of bar() to non-private solves it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;class A {&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    int counter = 0&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    protected def final foo() {&lt;br/&gt;
        bar &lt;/p&gt;
{
            counter
        }
&lt;p&gt;    }&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    private final String bar(Closure code) &lt;/p&gt;
{
        return &quot;Bar &quot; + code()
    }
&lt;p&gt;}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;class B extends A {}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;class C {}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;C.metaClass {&lt;br/&gt;
    mixin B&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;def c= new C()&lt;br/&gt;
c.foo()&lt;/p&gt;

</description>
